"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is using np.sinc() function which returns the sinc function of the input array. The sinc function is defined as sinc(x) = sin(pi*x)/(pi*x). So, sinc(0) is mathematically undefined but in numpy, sinc(0) is defined as 1. But sinc(1) is not equal to 0, it is approximately 0.63662. Therefore, the assertion sinc_result[1] == 0 will fail.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7,8c7,8\\nassert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n>assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], 0.63662), \\\"Results not equal to sinc(1)\\\"\"\n}"